  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nTechAnalogy needed stronger sales and marketing operations across social engagement, B2B acquisition, campaign execution, and education-program growth. The role required connecting marketing activity to measurable acquisition and registration outcomes.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe work moved from campaign tracking and engagement review into cross-channel B2C/B2B strategy, account reporting, market research, and A/B testing on marketing offers.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Campaign analytics:** analyzed engagement and campaign performance metrics to support 10+ new B2B acquisitions.\n- **Account liaison work:** served as the primary data liaison across 4 key accounts.\n- **Cross-channel campaign strategy:** coordinated B2C+B2B execution that drove roughly 20% increase in student registrations.\n- **Market research:** analyzed social-media engagement and participant demographics to support a 3-domain Robotics course pilot with 100+ enrollments.\n- **A/B testing:** tested marketing offers and lifted recurring lead-funnel conversion rates by roughly 5%.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe role connected SMO execution with sales operations, supporting 10+ B2B acquisitions, a roughly 20% quarterly lift in student registrations, 100+ Robotics course enrollments, and a roughly 5% improvement in recurring campaign conversions."
